data.description: Tudor style home on 3 lots in The Garden District featuring 4 Bedrooms with a possible 5 bedroom or upstairs bonus/recreation room and 3.5 baths! Formal living and dining, den, large kitchen with center island and bar seating as well as a breakfast area. Acacia wood counters, backlit upper kitchen cabinets with glass doors, stainless appliances including a gas range and built in microwave. (refrigerator is negotiable) walk in pantry, built in China cabinet and appliance garage. Primary en suite bath has a dual head walk in shower, oversized soaker tub, his and hers marble topped vanity sinks. Extensively renovated under 10 years ago with exceptional finishes and attention to detail this home includes custom paneled walls, multiple built ins, bookshelves, French style interior doors, 3 ventless gas fireplaces, shiplap and beaded board ceilings, board and baton walls, and wainscotting. Original refinished hardwood floors in formal rooms and bedrooms with natural slate floors in Den, halls, kitchen, and utility/mud room. Octagon Carrera marble tile floor in Guest bath. Large bedrooms with ample closets and plentiful storage space throughout the home. Covered back patio off of den and mud room, open patio in fenced back yard with vehicle access through double gate. Oversized 2 car garage with attached workshop (with more built ins) and a storage loft. Private courtyard off of mudroom and a separately fenced dog yard as well. Loaded with amenities and character, make an appointment to see this special home!
